      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Ans. B) Lunate</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Option B)</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong><img src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/02/12/screenshot-2024-02-12-143851.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"361\"></strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><ul><li><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>From lateral to medial and from proximal to distal:</strong></span><br><br><span style=\"color:red;font-size:14px;\"><strong>She Looks Too Pretty (Try To Catch Her):</strong></span><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">&nbsp;</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Scaphoid Lunate Triquetral Pisiform&nbsp;</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">(Trapezium Trapezoid Capitate Hamate)</span></p></li></ul><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Explanation:</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Option A. Trapezium.</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><img src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/02/12/screenshot-2024-02-12-143902.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"469\"></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Option C. Trapezoid.</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><img src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/02/12/screenshot-2024-02-12-143911.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"479\"></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Option D. Capitate.</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><img src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/02/12/screenshot-2024-02-12-143927.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"529\"></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Educational objective:</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><ul><li><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The structure marked in the given image is the carpal bone, Lunate.</span></p></li></ul>",
